		<page mustlisten="false" obfuscate="false" length="16824">
			<text><![CDATA[In the southern hemisphere polar air comes from the South. Trade winds blow towards the Equator,  on both sides of the zone with no wind. This is the Equatorial trough , also called the Doldrums. The Roaring Forties are gale winds in the southern hemisphere. ]]></text>
